Integer.Name: SensorWidth
Integer.Description: Full width of image sensor.

Integer.Name: SensorHeight
Integer.Description: Full height of image sensor.

Integer.Name: BinningHorizontal
Integer.Description: Binning in horizontal direction. Binning is the summing of charge of adjacent pixels.

Integer.Name: BinningVertical
Integer.Description: Binning in vertical direction. Binning is the summing of charge of adjacent pixels.

Integer.Name: StreamBytesPerSecond
Integer.Description: Bandwidth allocation: the camera will consume up to this bandwidth, in bytes per second. You must set this value if multiple cameras share the same ethernet adapter, otherwise data will be lost. The sum of all StreamBytesPerSecond values of all cameras must not exceed the available bandwidth.

Enumeration.Name: BandwidthControlMode
Enumeration.Description: Bandwidth allocation can be controlled by StreamBytesPerSecond, or by register SCPD0. If you do not understand SCPD0 and how this driver uses this register, leave this set to "StreamBytesPerSecond".

Enumeration.Name: StreamHoldEnable
Enumeration.Description: Control on-camera image storage; this control is like a "pause" button for the image stream. When enabled, images remain stored on the camera, and are not transmitted to the host. When disabled, the image stream resumes, and any stored images are sent to the host.

Integer.Name: StreamHoldCapacity
Integer.Description: Maximum number of images (for the current size and format) which can be stored on the camera when StreamHold is enabled.

Integer.Name: WidthMax
Integer.Description: Maximum image width for the current image mode. Horizontal binning, for example, will change this value.

Integer.Name: HeightMax
Integer.Description: Maximum image height for the current image mode. Vertical binning, for example, will change this value.

Enumeration.Name: PixelFormat
Enumeration.Description: Format of the image data.

Integer.Name: Width
Integer.Description: Width of image, in pixels.

Integer.Name: Height
Integer.Description: Height of image, in pixels.

Integer.Name: OffsetX
Integer.Description: Starting column of the readout region (relative to the first column of the sensor) in pixels.

Integer.Name: OffsetY
Integer.Description: Starting row of the readout region (relative to the first row of the sensor) in pixels.

Integer.Name: PayloadSize
Integer.Description: Size of images, in bytes, for the current format and size.

Command.Name: AcquisitionStart
Command.Description: Start acquisition. Before image acquisition can occur, acquisition must be started, either by a hardware trigger or this software command.

Command.Name: AcquisitionStop
Command.Description: Stop acquisition. Acquisition will stop after acquisition of the current frame is complete.

Command.Name: AcquisitionAbort
Command.Description: Abort acquisition. Acquisition will stop immediately, but a partially transferred image will be completed.

Enumeration.Name: AcquisitionMode
Enumeration.Description: The acquisition mode determines the behavior of the camera when acquisition start is triggered. "Continuous" mode: the camera will acquire images until acquisition stop is triggered. "SingleFrame" mode: the camera will acquire a single image. "MultiFrame" mode: the camera will acquire the number of images specified by AcquisitionFrameCount. "Recorder" mode: the camera will run continuously, and when the recorder event is triggered, send pre-trigger and post-trigger images to the host.

Integer.Name: AcquisitionFrameCount
Integer.Description: This is the number of images to acquire when in MultiFrame and Recorder acquisition modes.

Integer.Name: RecorderPreEventCount
Integer.Description: This is the number of pre-event images to acquire in the Recorder acquisition mode. This must be less than or equal to AcquisitionFrameCount.

Converter.Name: AcquisitionFrameRateAbs
Converter.Description: Frame rate, in frames per second. This is applicable when either the FrameStart trigger mode is disabled, or the FrameStart trigger source is FixedRate. Depending on the exposure duration, the camera may not achieve the frame rate set here.

Converter.Name: AcquisitionFrameRateLimit
Converter.Description: This is the maximum frame rate possible for the current exposure duration and image format.

Enumeration.Name: TriggerSelector
Enumeration.Description: Select a trigger here, then use the controls {TriggerMode, TriggerSoftware, TriggerSource, TriggerActivation, TriggerDelayAbs} to setup and read the trigger attributes. FrameStart is the trigger which starts each image (when acquisition is running). AcquisitionStart is the trigger which starts the acquisition process.

Enumeration.Name: TriggerMode
Enumeration.Description: Enable or disable this trigger. Note: when the FrameStart trigger is disabled, images are triggered at a fixed rate specified by AcquisitionFrameRateAbs.

Command.Name: TriggerSoftware
Command.Description: This software command effects a trigger.

Enumeration.Name: TriggerSource
Enumeration.Description: Source of trigger, when TriggerMode is On. This might be an hardware trigger, a fixed rate generator, or software trigger only.

Enumeration.Name: TriggerActivation
Enumeration.Description: Type of activation, for hardware triggers. This controls edge/level and polarity sensitivities.

Float.Name: TriggerDelayAbs
Float.Description: Delay from hardware trigger activation to trigger effect, in microseconds.

Integer.Name: DSPSubregionLeft
Integer.Description: The DSP subregion is the area of the image used for measurements in "auto-" functions such as auto-exposure and auto-gain. DSPSubregionLeft is the left column, relative to the current image region.

Integer.Name: DSPSubregionTop
Integer.Description: The DSP subregion is the area of the image used for measurements in "auto-" functions such as auto-exposure and auto-gain. DSPSubregionLeft is the top row, relative to the current image region.

Integer.Name: DSPSubregionRight
Integer.Description: The DSP subregion is the area of the image used for measurements in "auto-" functions such as auto-exposure and auto-gain. DSPSubregionLeft is the right column, relative to the current image region. For convenience, this value may be higher than the maximum Width.

Integer.Name: DSPSubregionBottom
Integer.Description: The DSP subregion is the area of the image used for measurements in "auto-" functions such as auto-exposure and auto-gain. DSPSubregionLeft is the bottom row, relative to the current image region. For convenience, this value may be higher than the maximum Height.

Enumeration.Name: ExposureMode
Enumeration.Description: Method of control for exposure duration. Timed mode: exposure duration is set by ExposureTimeAbs.

Enumeration.Name: ExposureAuto
Enumeration.Description: Automatic exposure mode. Off: automatic mode is off. Once: auto-exposure occurs until target is achieved, then ExposureAuto returns to Off. Continuous: auto-exposure always runs.

Integer.Name: ExposureAutoTarget
Integer.Description: When ExposureAutoAlg is Mean, this is the target image mean value, in percent. Higher values result in brighter images.

Enumeration.Name: ExposureAutoAlg
Enumeration.Description: Algorithm used for auto-exposure. Mean: target a particular mean value of all measured pixels in the image. FitRange: adjust the maximum pixel value to fit the sensor range.

Integer.Name: ExposureAutoMin
Integer.Description: Minimum auto-exposure value, in microseconds.

Integer.Name: ExposureAutoMax
Integer.Description: Maximum auto-exposure value, in microseconds.

Integer.Name: ExposureAutoRate
Integer.Description: Rate of exposure adjustments, from 1 (slowest) to 100 (fastest). Use this control to slow down the auto-exposure adjustments.

Integer.Name: ExposureAutoOutliers
Integer.Description: Number of upper outliers to discard before calculating exposure adjustments. This is in ten-thousandths of the number pixels in the image.

Integer.Name: ExposureAutoAdjustTol
Integer.Description: Tolerance, in percent, allowed from the ideal exposure value, within which the auto-exposure does not run. This prevents needless small adjustments from occurring each image.

Enumeration.Name: GainSelector
Enumeration.Description: (GenICam boilerplate. Always All.)

Integer.Name: GainRaw
Integer.Description: Gain value of analog A/D stage. Units are usually in dB.

Enumeration.Name: GainAuto
Enumeration.Description: Automatic exposure mode. Off: automatic mode is off. Once: auto-gain occurs until target is achieved, then GainAuto returns to Off. Continuous: auto-gain always runs.

Integer.Name: GainAutoTarget
Integer.Description: This is the target image mean value, in percent.

Integer.Name: GainAutoMin
Integer.Description: Minimum auto-gain value.

Integer.Name: GainAutoMax
Integer.Description: Maximum auto-gain value.

Integer.Name: GainAutoRate
Integer.Description: Rate of gain adjustments, from 1 (slowest) to 100 (fastest). Use this control to slow down the auto-gain adjustments.

Integer.Name: GainAutoOutliers
Integer.Description: Number of upper outliers to discard before calculating gain adjustments. This is in ten-thousandths of the number pixels in the image.

Integer.Name: GainAutoAdjustTol
Integer.Description: Tolerance, in percent, allowed from the ideal gain value, within which the auto-gain does not run. This prevents needless small adjustments from occurring each image.

Enumeration.Name: BalanceRatioSelector
Enumeration.Description: Select the Red or Blue channel to adjust with BalanceRatioAbs.

Float.Name: BalanceRatioAbs
Float.Description: Adjust the gain of the red or blue channel (see BalanceRatioSelector). The green channel gain is always 1.00.

Enumeration.Name: BalanceWhiteAuto
Enumeration.Description: Automatic whitebalance mode. Off: automatic mode is off. Once: auto-whitebalance occurs until target is achieved, then BalanceWhiteAuto returns to Off. Continuous: auto-whitebalance always runs.

Integer.Name: BalanceWhiteAutoRate
Integer.Description: Rate of white balance adjustments, from 1 (slowest) to 100 (fastest). Use this control to slow down the auto-whitebalance adjustments.

Integer.Name: BalanceWhiteAutoAdjustTol
Integer.Description: Tolerance, in percent, allowed from the ideal whitebalance values, within which the auto-whitebalance does not run. This prevents needless small adjustments from occurring each image.

Enumeration.Name: IrisMode
Enumeration.Description: Set the iris mode. Disabled: no iris control. Video: enable video iris. VideoOpen: fully open a video iris. VideoClosed: fully close a video iris.

Integer.Name: IrisAutoTarget
Integer.Description: This is the target image mean value, in percent.

Integer.Name: IrisVideoLevel
Integer.Description: Current video-iris level, in approximately mV pp; read only. When calibrating a video lens, this value should fall between IrisVideoLevelMin and IrisVideoLevelMax.

Integer.Name: IrisVideoLevelMin
Integer.Description: Minimum video iris level output by the camera, in approximately mV pp. A higher minimum value slows the adjustment time but prevents excessive overshoot.

Integer.Name: IrisVideoLevelMax
Integer.Description: Maximum video iris level output by the camera, in approximately mV pp. A lower minimum value slows the adjustment time but prevents excessive overshoot.

Enumeration.Name: DefectMaskColumnEnable
Enumeration.Description: Enable masking of defective columns. Defective columns are detected and recorded at the factory.

Enumeration.Name: DefectMaskPixelEnable
Enumeration.Description: Enable masking of defective pixels. Defective pixels are detected and recorded at the factory.

Integer.Name: SyncInLevels
Integer.Description: Momentary logic levels of the hardware line inputs.

Integer.Name: SyncOutLevels
Integer.Description: Output levels of hardware sync outputs, for output(s) in GPO mode. (Note: SyncOutPolarity can invert these values.)

Enumeration.Name: SyncOutSelector
Enumeration.Description: Select the sync-out line to control with {SyncOutSource, SyncOutPolarity}.

Enumeration.Name: SyncOutSource
Enumeration.Description: Signal source of the sync-out line specified by SyncOutSelector. GPO: general purpose output. AcquisitionTriggerReady: acquisition trigger may occur. FrameTriggerReady: frame trigger may occur. Exposing: exposure in progress. FrameReadout: image readout in progress. Imaging: exposure or frame readout in progress. Acquiring: acquisition is running. LineIn: external line input. Strobe: source is strobe timing unit.

Enumeration.Name: SyncOutPolarity
Enumeration.Description: Polarity applied to the sync-out line specified by SyncOutSelector.

Enumeration.Name: StrobeSource
Enumeration.Description: Signal source of the strobe timing unit. See SyncOutSource for descriptions.

Enumeration.Name: StrobeDurationMode
Enumeration.Description: Mode of the strobe timing unit. Source: strobe duration is the same as source duration. Controlled: strobe duration is set by StrobeDuration.

Integer.Name: StrobeDelay
Integer.Description: Delay from strobe trigger to strobe output, in microseconds.

Integer.Name: StrobeDuration
Integer.Description: Duration of strobe, in microseconds.

Enumeration.Name: UserSetSelector
Enumeration.Description: Select a user set, for loading or saving camera parameters.

Command.Name: UserSetLoad
Command.Description: Load camera parameters from the user set specified by UserSetSelector.

Command.Name: UserSetSave
Command.Description: Save camera parameters to the user set specified by UserSetSelector.

Enumeration.Name: UserSetDefaultSelector
Enumeration.Description: On power-up or reset, this user set is loaded.

StringReg.Name: DeviceFirmwareVersion
StringReg.Description: Firmware version of this Prosilica GigE camera.
